				<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1640f746d0fec55ff6e5b5a770b50fdd?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1640f746d0fec55ff6e5b5a770b50fdd?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.swantower.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Marie Brennan</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-500875">
				January 9, 2017 at 18:18					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>Thanks for letting me know! I guess it partly comes down to how one views the &#8220;Best Series&#8221; award &#8212; I personally lean toward viewing it as a way of saying &#8220;we think this series is worthy of recognition,&#8221; and once you&#8217;ve said that, you don&#8217;t need to say it again. Letting a series win more than once, even with that proposed restriction in place, makes me feel like the award is more like &#8220;Best Series That Had a New Installment This Year,&#8221; and I&#8217;m much less interested in that.</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=500875#respond' data-commentid="500875" data-postid="2841" data-belowelement="comment-500875" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Marie Brennan'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
			</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
